From f9cabe527b3c75aacea39931357c6fa5615b966f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 23:27:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix poker gameplay bugs and improve betting/lobby UI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Gameplay / engine fixes (server.js):
- Fix broken all-in: an all-in raise now correctly re-opens the
  betting round for everyone else (the old code compared p.bet to a
  curBet it had just overwritten, so the branch was dead).
- Stop repetitive/unnecessary checks: after a raise the queue no
  longer wraps back around to the raiser, and all-in players (0 chips)
  are no longer asked to act again.
- Add real side pots: short-stack all-ins are settled in layered pots
  so a player can only win the portion they contested.
- Heads-up blinds: the dealer is now the small blind and acts first
  preflop, per standard rules.
- Track each player's total commitment for correct pot settlement and
  per-player winnings in the hand log.

Seating:
- A player is now locked to a single seat. take_seat moves the
  existing player instead of creating duplicate seats, and seat
  changes are only allowed between hands.
- Table size (max players) is configurable; join/seat respect it.

UI:
- Customizable create-table form (free numeric starting chips, small
  and big blind, and table size) matching the settings panel style.
- Reworked betting bar: synced slider + number input, dynamic
  Bet/Raise labels, ½/¾/Pot/Max sizing buttons, and controls that
  hide when a raise isn't possible.
- Settings panel can set the default (rebuy) starting stack.

Also added a .gitignore for node_modules.
